seal               : Gunpei Yokoi's final design, finished after his death, the WonderSwan was a Japan-only handheld that fought the Game Boy on Yokoi's home turf: ruthless efficiency. A 16-bit CPU, play in both portrait and landscape, and a single AA battery that lasted around thirty hours.
